        <content><![CDATA[ <h1 class="title topictitle1">Create text index configuration</h1>  <div class="body conbody">  <p class="p">Text analysis begins with indexing the text. Text indexing is defined on      indicator sources, to allow for the reuse of a single index configuration by many indicators. </p><div class="p">When you set up text analytics, you decide on:<ul class="ul" id="pa-text-index-configurations__d42064e48"><li class="li">Which fields in an indicator source to index.</li><li class="li">Which indicators to apply a text index configuration to.</li><li class="li">Which stop words to exclude from analysis.</li><li class="li">Keywords for default drilldowns.</li></ul></div><p class="p">When you have set up text analytics, create a widget to      visualize the text and include the widget in a dashboard.</p> </div> <div class="related-links"><div class="relinfo"><div class="reltitle">Related information<br /><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:PA-Set-Up-Text-Analytics" target="_blank">Set up text analytics</a></div><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:PA-Text-Analytics-Stop-Words" target="_blank">Select text analytics stop words</a></div><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:PA_text-analytics-keywords" target="_blank">Select keywords for default drilldowns</a></div><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:PA-Create-Text-Widget" target="_blank">Create a text widget</a></div></div></div></div>]]></content>
